ENTRY            41785   20250915   20260518   20260518       4228
SUBENT        41785001   20250915   20260518   20260518       4228
BIB                 13         52
TITLE      Measurement of yields and angular distributions of
           gamma-quanta from the interaction of 14.1 MeV neutrons
           with oxygen, phosphorus, and sulfur
AUTHOR     (D.N.Grozdanov,N.A.Fedorov,S.Dabylova,Yu.N.Kopach,
           V.R.Skoy, I.N.Ruskov,T.Yu.Tretyakova,C.Hramco,
           P.I.Kharlamov,G.V.Pampushik,P.G.Filonchik,A.V.Andreev)
INSTITUTE  (4ZZZDUB) D.N.Grozdanov,N.A.Fedorov,S.Dabylova,
           Yu.N.Kopach,V.R.Skoy,T.Yu.Tretyakova,C.Hramco,
           P.I.Kharlamov,P.G.Filonchik1,A.V.Andreev
           (3BULBLA) I.N.Ruskov,D.N.Grozdanov
           (4RUSMOS) N.A.Fedorov,T.Yu.Tretyakova, P.I.Kharlamov,
           G.V.Pampushik
           (4KASATN) S.Dabylova
           (4MLDMLD) Inst.of Chemistry of Moldova, Chisinau,
           Republic of Moldova.
           C.Hramco
           (4RUSMFT) P.G.Filonchik
REFERENCE  (J,CPH/C,48,034003,2024) Issue 3. In English.
           #doi:10.1088/1674-1137/ad147e
FACILITY   (NGEN,4ZZZDUB) Portable ING-27 neutron generator
            at TANGRA (TAgged Neutrons and Gamma RAys) facility.
INC-SOURCE (D-T) Deuterons of energy 80 - 100 keV on Ti tritide
           target. Maximal neutron flux 5.E+7 /sec.
METHOD     (ASSOP) Neutron - 3.5 MeV-alpha from d+t -> n+alpha
           reaction (tagged neutron method).
           (COINC) Alpha - gamma coincidences.
DETECTOR   (PS) Position-sensitive alpha-particle detector placed
           in the ING-27 neutron tube at a distance of 100 mm from
           the target consists of 16 (8+8) mutually perpendicular
           semiconductor strips, each 6 mm wide and 55 mm long.
           The overlapping strips form 64 (8x8) pixels with pixel
           size of 6x6 mm.
           (BGO) Detector system "Romasha":
            18 scintillation detectors based on BGO crystals
            ( Bi(4)Ge(3)O(12) ), for measurement of gamma-ray
           angular distributions. Resolution ~110 keV at 1.33 MeV.
           (HPGE) For gamma-yields measurement.
            Resolution ~1.9 keV at 1.33 MeV.
            HPGe crystal of 57.5 mm diameter, 66.6 mm thickness.
CORRECTION  Background was measured in separate experiment without
            sample.
            For random coincidences.
            For neutrons scattered on sample and surrounding.
            For gamma-quanta produced in interaction of neutrons
            with environment.
            For absorption of neutrons and gamma-quanta.
ADD-RES     Optical model parameterizations are given in Appendix
           of the article J,CPH/C,48,034003,2024.
COMMENT    Of authors.
           This work was supported by RSCF (23-12-00239).
STATUS     (APRVD) Approved by the author N.Fedorov.
HISTORY    (20250915C) M.M.
ENDBIB              52
COMMON               1          3
EN
MEV
 14.1
ENDCOMMON            3
ENDSUBENT           59
SUBENT        41785002   20250915   20260518   20260518       4228
BIB                  6         18
REACTION   ((8-O-16(N,A)6-C-13,,SPC)//(8-O-16(N,INL)8-O-16,,SPC))
            Intensity relative to that of 6129.9 keV gamma-line,
           taken per 100% in the article. Divided by 100
           by compiler to obtain NO-DIM units.
SAMPLE      P(2)O(5) - density 0.903 g/cm3, size 6x6x14 cm3,
           mass 455 g, purity > 99%, isotopic composition:
           31P -100 %, 16O - 99.757 %, 17O - 0.038%, 18O - 0.25%;
ANALYSIS   Gamma quanta yields Yi were defined by formula (3):
            Yi = Ni/N0, where
           Ni and N0 are the numbers of emitted gamma quanta with
           energy Ei and E0, respectively.
REL-REF    Data used for comparison:
            TALYS calculation,
           (N,,S.P.Simakov+,R,INDC(CCP)-413,1998)
           (N,20245001,K.Nyberg-Ponnert+,J,PS,4,165,1971)
ERR-ANALYS (ERR-SYS,,5.) Systematical uncertainty
           (ERR-S) Statistical uncertainty
STATUS     (TABLE,,D.N.Grozdanov,J,CPH/C,48,034003,2024) Table 3
