REACTION   (8-O-16(N,INL)8-O-16,PAR,DA,G,LEG/RS)
SAMPLE      P(2)O(5) - density 0.903 g/cm3, size 6x6x14 cm3,
           mass 455 g, purity > 99%, isotopic composition:
           31P -100 %, 16O - 99.757 %, 17O - 0.038%, 18O - 0.25%;
REL-REF    Data used for comparison:
            TALYS calculation, ENDF evaluation.
           (R,,D.Tilley+,J,NP/A,564,1,1993)
            Gamma-quanta energies, spin,parity, energy of initial
           and final levels.
ANALYSIS   Measured angular distributions
            (Fig.8 of CPH/C,48,034003,2024)
           were approximated :
           W(angle)=1+SUM(ai*Pi(cos(angle))) , i=2,4,...,
           Pi - Legendre polynomials.
